        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, pp. 106-107, n. <citedRange>73</citedRange>, pl. XX, fig. 28</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.68</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>016400</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, pp. <citedRange>196-197</citedRange> (typology), p. <citedRange>372</citedRange>, number 98 (text)</bibl>.</p>
                    <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>116, 120</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>38.1881</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64780"><name nymRef="#Λέντιχος"><supplied reason="lost">Λέν</supplied>τιχος</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62818"><name nymRef="#Ἀμμώνιος" type="patronymic">Ἀμμωνίω</name></persName></persName> <name type="festival" key="Karneia" nymRef="#Καρνῆια">Καρ<unclear>ν</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ῆια</supplied></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="τελεσφορέω"><supplied reason="lost">τελε</supplied>σφορέων</w> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w> 
                        <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέ<supplied reason="lost">θηκε</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62818"><name nymRef="#Ἀμμώνιος"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀμμ</supplied>ώνιον</name> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63725"><name nymRef="#Ἐπίχαρμος" type="patronymic">Ἐπιχάρμ<supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></name></persName></persName>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#rosamilia2023">Καρ<unclear>ν</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ῆια</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#IGCyr">Καρ<supplied reason="lost">νῆια</supplied></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverioDAI2">Κάρ<supplied reason="lost">νεια</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Lentikhos fils d'Ammonios, en accomplissant la <foreign rend="italic">telesphoria</foreign> des Karneia, a consacré comme dîme <supplied reason="subaudible">la statue d'</supplied>Ammônios fils d'Epikharmos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Lentichos son of Ammonios, when celebrating the <foreign rend="italic">telesphoria</foreign> of Karneia, offered as tithe <supplied reason="subaudible">the statue of</supplied> Ammonios son of Epicharmos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Lentichos figlio di Ammonios, mentre celebrava la <foreign rend="italic">telesphoria</foreign> delle Karneia, ha offerto come decima <supplied reason="subaudible">la statua di</supplied> Ammonios figlio di Epicharmos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>قدم لينتيخوس بن أمونيوس (تمثالاً ل) أمونيوس بن إبيخارموس كعِشر (ضريبة)، عند الاحتفال بالتيليسفوريا الكارنيا.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Lentichos seems to have dedicated the statue of his father Ammonios, as suspected by <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>116, 120</citedRange></bibl>, who dated the 
                    dedication between 370 and 360 BC. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> pushes the bracket down to 250 without providing arguments.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
